Here's a simple web app that showcases the top ten toilets in the world, complete with embedded CSS and JavaScript in a single HTML file. This includes basic styling and a simple interactive feature that lets you see more details about each toilet when clicked.

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Top Ten Toilets in the World</title>
    <style>
        body {
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
            background-color: #f0f0f0;
            margin: 0;
            padding: 20px;
        }
        h1 {
            text-align: center;
            color: #333;
        }
        .toilet-list {
            max-width: 600px;
            margin: auto;
            background: white;
            border-radius: 8px;
            box-shadow: 0 0 10px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
            padding: 20px;
        }
        .toilet-item {
            margin: 15px 0;
            padding: 10px;
            background-color: #e0e7ff;
            border-radius: 5px;
            cursor: pointer;
            transition: background-color 0.3s;
        }
        .toilet-item:hover {
            background-color: #c7d2fe;
        }
        .details {
            display: none;
            margin-top: 10px;
            background-color: #f1f5f9;
            padding: 10px;
            border-radius: 5px;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>

<h1>Top Ten Toilets in the World</h1>
<div class="toilet-list">
    <div class="toilet-item" onclick="toggleDetails('details1')">
        Toilet 1: The Japanese Washlet
        <div id="details1" class="details">The Washlet is famous for its advanced features like heated seats and bidet functionality.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="toilet-item" onclick="toggleDetails('details2')">
        Toilet 2: The Seliga
        <div id="details2" class="details">This luxurious toilet offers advanced technology including automatic lid opening and flushing.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="toilet-item" onclick="toggleDetails('details3')">
        Toilet 3: The Infinity Toilet
        <div id="details3" class="details">Known for its unique design, the Infinity Toilet aims to integrate art and technology.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="toilet-item" onclick="toggleDetails('details4')">
        Toilet 4: The TOTO Neorest
        <div id="details4" class="details">Combines luxury with sustainability, featuring automatic cleaning and deodorizing systems.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="toilet-item" onclick="toggleDetails('details5')">
        Toilet 5: The Numi
        <div id="details5" class="details">Numi offers smart features such as foot warming, ambient lighting, and more for comfort and convenience.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="toilet-item" onclick="toggleDetails('details6')">
        Toilet 6: The Kohler Veil
        <div id="details6" class="details">A minimalist design with advanced cleaning functions and efficient flushing technology.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="toilet-item" onclick="toggleDetails('details7')">
        Toilet 7: The American Standard ActiClean
        <div id="details7" class="details">Provides a self-cleaning feature that eliminates odors and stains effortlessly.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="toilet-item" onclick="toggleDetails('details8')">
        Toilet 8: The Ceramique Toilet
        <div id="details8" class="details">Features stylish designs made from beautiful ceramic materials that enhance any bathroom decor.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="toilet-item" onclick="toggleDetails('details9')">
        Toilet 9: The BioToilet
        <div id="details9" class="details">An eco-friendly solution that uses composting technology to minimize waste.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="toilet-item" onclick="toggleDetails('details10')">
        Toilet 10: The Swisssan Toilets
        <div id="details10" class="details">Combines Swiss engineering with environmentally friendly technology for sustainable waste management.</div>
    </div>
</div>

<script>
    function toggleDetails(id) {
        const details = document.getElementById(id);
        if (details.style.display === "none" || details.style.display === "") {
            details.style.display = "block";
        } else {
            details.style.display = "none";
        }
    }

    // Initialize all details to be hidden
    document.querySelectorAll('.details').forEach(detail => {
        detail.style.display = 'none';
    });
</script>

</body>
</html>
```

### How to Use:
1. Copy the entire code block above.
2. Paste it into a text editor of your choice (like Notepad, Sublime Text, etc.).
3. Save the file with a `.html` extension (e.g., `top_ten_toilets.html`).
4. Open the saved HTML file in a web browser to see the app in action. 

You can click on each toilet entry to toggle the display of its details. Enjoy!
